      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-09-11T21:31:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "set your log level higher.",
      "parentUuid": "fa98f980_dcc23c52",
      "revId": "abaf9e2b2c41a167b79388aa3c4f482f81ae7887",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa98f980_dd3a1acc",
        "filename": "monasca/dispatcher/kafka_queue.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 124,
      "author": {
        "id": 2419
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-09-12T17:42:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Keeping log files semi-usable and uncluttered is extremely useful. Think about this, there is a big that shows up in production. You want to enable debug level logging. \n\nIs it really important to you to have every message logged that is was successfully sent. If your code is deployed in production you\u0027ll fill up your log file and make it impossible to see the forest through the trees.\n\nI think logging the messages that weren\u0027t sent successfully might be OK, but every successful message, that isn\u0027t a DEBUG level logging IMHO, that would be trace level debugging.\n\nThe OpenStack community talks about appropriate log messages and how cluttered up the log files are already.",
      "revId": "abaf9e2b2c41a167b79388aa3c4f482f81ae7887",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa98f980_00535217",
        "filename": "monasca/dispatcher/kafka_queue.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 124,
      "author": {
        "id": 2860
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-09-12T20:20:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think at the beginning, when we try things, it is good to have more message.\nI added these to especially make you guys know what is going on when bad\nthings happen. I normally do not write that many debug messages as they\ndo cost some cpu cycles. We can remove some of these later.",
      "parentUuid": "fa98f980_dd3a1acc",
      "revId": "abaf9e2b2c41a167b79388aa3c4f482f81ae7887",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa98f980_bcc1f830",
        "filename": "monasca/dispatcher/kafka_queue.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 2419
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-09-11T20:57:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems to me that this should be\n\n10.4.1 400 Bad Request\n\nThe request could not be understood by the server due to malformed syntax. The client SHOULD NOT repeat the request without modifications.\n\n406 is used in this situation\n\n10.4.7 406 Not Acceptable\n\nThe resource identified by the request is only capable of generating response entities which have content characteristics not acceptable according to the accept headers sent in the request.\n\nUnless it was a HEAD request, the response SHOULD include an entity containing a list of available entity characteristics and location(s) from which the user or user agent can choose the one most appropriate. The entity format is specified by the media type given in the Content-Type header field. Depending upon the format and the capabilities of the user agent, selection of the most appropriate choice MAY be performed automatically. However, this specification does not define any standard for such automatic selection.\n\n      Note: HTTP/1.1 servers are allowed to return responses which are\n      not acceptable according to the accept headers sent in the\n      request. In some cases, this may even be preferable to sending a\n      406 response. User agents are encouraged to inspect the headers of\n      an incoming response to determine if it is acceptable.\nIf the response could be unacceptable, a user agent SHOULD temporarily stop receipt of more data and query the user for a decision on further actions.\n\n\nAs this was a problem parsing the incoming JSON body that would be that the JSON is malformed.",
      "revId": "abaf9e2b2c41a167b79388aa3c4f482f81ae7887",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa98f980_c196d093",
        "filename": "monasca/dispatcher/kafka_queue.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 2860
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-09-11T21:31:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "not valid json is not acceptable by this service. I am ok to change it to 400.\nI think that 406 is better.",
      "parentUuid": "fa98f980_bcc1f830",
      "revId": "abaf9e2b2c41a167b79388aa3c4f482f81ae7887",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa98f980_9c3d142e",
        "filename": "monasca/dispatcher/kafka_queue.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 135,
      "author": {
